  First Horizon Corporation – Memphis, TN | Lead Java Full Stack Developer May 2023 - Present
  Project Overview
  Working on enterprise digital banking and internal platforms supporting customer onboarding, transaction processing, compliance workflows, and operational tools used by business and risk teams across the organization.
  Roles & Responsibilities
  Designing and developing Java Spring Boot–based microservices to support core banking workflows such as customer profile management, transaction validation, and internal approvals.
  Building an
  d maintaining RESTful APIs consumed by both internal applications and external partner systems, ensuring secure and reliable data exchange.
  Developing modern Angular UI components for internal users, focusing on usability, accessibility, and consistent user experience across modules.
  Collaborating closely with business analysts, compliance teams, and product owners to understand client requirements and translate them into technical solutions.
  Implementing Spring Security with OAuth2 and JWT to meet banking security standards and protect sensitive customer and transaction data.
  Working on AWS-hosted applications, leveraging services such as EC2, S3, RDS, and CloudWatch for application hosting, storage, and monitoring.
  Participating in legacy application modernization, breaking down monolithic services into smaller, maintainable microservices.
  Integrating AI-assisted validation logic to automatically detect unusual transaction patterns, duplicate records, and data inconsistencies before processing.
  Using rule-based automation and AI-supported checks to reduce manual review effort for compliance and operational teams.
  Implementing Kafka-based messaging for asynchronous processing, audit logging, and system-to-system notifications.
  Writing optimized SQL queries and JPA repositories, focusing on performance, data integrity, and transactional consistency.
  Actively contributing to code reviews, enforcing coding standards, and improving overall code quality across the team.
  Supporting CI/CD pipelines using Jenkins and Docker, enabling smooth deployments across development, QA, and production environments.
  Working closely with QA teams to support integration testing, defect resolution, and release validation.
  Participating in Agile ceremonies including sprint planning, backlog grooming, and retrospectives, ensuring on-time delivery of client commitments.
  Providing production support and troubleshooting issues related to APIs, UI behavior, and backend processing.
  Mentoring junior developers and onboarding new team members into project architecture and development standards.
  eBay – Austin, TX | Java Full Stack Developer May 2021 – April 2023
  Project Overview
  Worked on large-scale e-commerce platforms supporting seller management, order processing, pricing workflows, and internal operational tools used by business and support teams across global marketplaces.
  Roles & Responsibilities
  Developed and maintained Java Spring Boot microservices supporting core e-commerce workflows such as order lifecycle management, seller onboarding, and catalog updates.
