  Implemented asynchronous processing using Apache Kafka for order events, inventory updates, and system notifications.
  Integrated backend services with pricing, promotions, and recommendation systems to support dynamic marketplace behavior.
  Used SQL and JPA/Hibernate extensively to design queries, manage transactional data, and ensure data consistency across services.
  Contributed to fault-tolerant microservices design, implementing retry mechanisms, circuit breakers, and graceful error handling.
  Leveraged AWS services for application hosting, storage, and monitoring, working with EC2, S3, RDS, and CloudWatch.
  Participated in cloud migration and service refactoring efforts, helping decouple legacy components into independently deployable services.
  Applied AI-assisted logic for data validation and pattern checks in seller activity and order flows to identify anomalies and reduce manual reviews.
  Worked with rule-based automation and smart filtering to flag suspicious seller behavior and duplicate transactions.
  Improved test coverage by writing unit and integration tests using JUnit and Mockito, supporting stable production releases.
  Supported production deployments and on-call activities, troubleshooting API failures, UI issues, and data inconsistencies.
  Collaborated daily with QA, DevOps, and Site Reliability teams to resolve defects and ensure smooth releases.
  Actively participated in Agile ceremonies, including sprint planning, backlog refinement, and retrospectives.
  Documented service behavior, API contracts, and onboarding guides for new team members.
  Followed secure coding practices and internal compliance standards for enterprise-grade applications.
